RCW 53.57.060

Applicable laws. (Effective until January 1, 2026.)

A port development authority created under this chapter must comply with applicable laws including, but not limited to, the following:(1) Requirements concerning local government audits by the state auditor and applicable accounting requirements set forth in chapter 43.09 RCW;(2) The public records act, chapter 42.56 RCW;(3) Prohibitions on using facilities for campaign purposes under RCW 42.17A.555;(4) The open public meetings act, chapter 42.30 RCW;(5) The code of ethics for municipal officers under chapter 42.23 RCW; and(6) Local government whistleblower protection laws set forth in chapter 42.41 RCW.

A port development authority created under this chapter must comply with applicable laws including, but not limited to, the following:

(1) Requirements concerning local government audits by the state auditor and applicable accounting requirements set forth in chapter 43.09 RCW;

(2) The public records act, chapter 42.56 RCW;

(3) Prohibitions on using facilities for campaign purposes under RCW 42.17A.555;

(4) The open public meetings act, chapter 42.30 RCW;

(5) The code of ethics for municipal officers under chapter 42.23 RCW; and

(6) Local government whistleblower protection laws set forth in chapter 42.41 RCW.

[ 2015 c 35 s 7.]

